-- Michinoku Bank Provides 2 Billion Yen Loan for Eurus Solar Plant
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-10-16T07:10:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-16/michinoku-bank-provides-2-billion-yen-loan-for-eurus-solar-plant.html
Michinoku Bank Ltd. (8350) , a regional
bank, will provide 2 billion yen ($20 million) in loans for a
solar power plant Eurus Energy Holdings Corp. is building in the
northern prefecture of Aomori.  The bank, based in Aomori, will provide the loan as part of
39.4 billion yen project financing with 13 other banks led by
the  Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ , Michinoku said in a statement
yesterday.  Eurus, a Japanese developer of solar and wind projects, is
building the 115-megawatt station in Rokkasho Village which will
start operations in November 2015, the company said in August.  Aomori Bank Ltd. (8342) , another partner in the 39.4 billion yen
syndicated loan, will provide a 4 billion yen loan, the Aomori-based regional bank said in a separate statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
